    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect parameter order and array sizing in polar_encoder_dci function\n\n### Summary\nThe NR polar encoder for DCI contained multiple issues that caused incorrect encoding behavior. The main problem was an incorrect function call in the testbench that passed parameters in the wrong order, causing the RNTI value to be interpreted as a parameter struct.\n\nAdditionally, the function had hardcoded array sizing that could lead to buffer overflows or memory waste, and the CRC scrambling offset was not clearly calculated.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/TESTBENCH/polartest.c`: Fixed parameter order in polar_encoder_dci call\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrPolar_tools/nr_polar_encoder.c`: Fixed array size calculation and made scrambling offset explicit\n\nUnder certain conditions with specific RNTI values, this would cause the encoder to access invalid memory addresses or produce incorrect encoded bits that fail CRC checks at the receiver.\n"
}